translated: Holmberg, Sigurd Natanael was a high school teacher in Gothenburg, born on May 18, 1898 in Gothenburg to August H. and Charlotta Holmberg. He completed his primary school teacher's examination in 1919, graduated from Gothenburg's high school with Latin in 1921, earned a Bachelor of Arts degree in Gothenburg in 1926, a Master of Arts degree in 1927, a Licentiate of Philosophy degree in 1938, and completed a trial year at Gothenburg's high school for natural sciences in 1930. He traveled to Germany in 1921 and 1925, to England in 1922, 1923, 1924, and 1936. He worked as a subject teacher at Gothenburg's municipal middle school from 1928 to 1939, and as a teacher of mother tongue and German at Majorna's high school in Gothenburg since 1939. He was the chairman of Gothenburg's student gymnastics and sports association from 1923 to 1924 and Gothenburg's higher education sports association from 1928 to 1929. He married but no information was given about his spouse.
